Here is a summarized version of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

 Requests the Secretary-General to extend the Group of Experts until 31 December 2008.

 Mandates the Group of Experts to:
- Examine and analyze information gathered by MONUC
- Gather and analyze information on arms flows and related networks
- Recommend ways to improve States' capabilities to implement measures
- Report to the Council by 15 August and 15 November 2008
- Keep the Committee updated on its activities
- Provide a list of those who have violated measures with supporting evidence
- Assist the Committee in designating individuals

 Requests MONUC and the Group of Experts to focus on North and South Kivu and Ituri.

 Requests cooperation between the Government of the Democratic Republic of Congo, other Governments, MONUC, and the Group of Experts.

 Demands full cooperation with the Group of Experts, ensuring their safety and access to information.

 Decides to review measures by 31 December 2008, considering progress in security sector reform and disarmament.

 Decides to remain seized of the matter.
